title: JUI Candidate Sardar Khan wins PK-21 election
content:
ISLAMABAD, Feb 9 (APP): Jamat-e-Islami Pakistan (JUI) Candidate Sardar Khan has won the Khyber Pakhtunkhwa Assembly election from PK-21, Bajaur-III by securing 16,844 votes.
According to the unofficial result issued by the Returning Officer/ECP, his runner-up an Independent Candidate Ajmal Khan who bagged 15,713 votes.
Overall voters turn-out remained 29.4 per cent.
